'''性交'''（{{lang-en|Sexual intercourse}}），也有'''陰道交'''（vaginal sex）、'''阴道性交'''（vaginal intercourse）之稱<ref name="Weiten, 2008">{{cite book|title=Psychology Applied to Modern Life: Adjustment in the 21st Century|isbn=0495553395|publisher=Cengage Learning|year=2008|pages=422–423|accessdate=2012-01-05|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Y6QRJb40C84C&pg=PA422&lpg=PA422|author1=Wayne Weiten|author2=Margaret A. Lloyd|author3=Dana S. Dunn|author4=Elizabeth Yost Hammer|quote=Vaginal intercourse, known more technically as coitus, involves inserting the penis into the vagina and (typically) pelvic thrusting. ... The man-above, or "missionary," position is the most common sex position.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131231143609/http://books.google.com/books?id=Y6QRJb40C84C&pg=PA422&lpg=PA422|archive-date=2013-12-31|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Alters">{{cite book | author = Sandra Alters | author2 = Wendy Schiff | title = Essential Concepts for Healthy Living | publisher = Jones & Bartlett Publishers | year = 2012 | pages = 180–181 | accessdate = 2013-08-31 | isbn = 1449630626 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=VegUiVbruBMC&pg=PA180 | quote = Most heterosexuals are familiar with the notion of 'having sex' or sexual intercourse as vaginal sex, the insertion of a penis into a vagina. Vaginal sex, or coitus, is the most common and popular form of intimate sexual activity between partners. | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20131231143642/http://books.google.com/books?id=VegUiVbruBMC&pg=PA180 | archive-date = 2013-12-31 | dead-url = no }}</ref>，指的是將一般為[[勃起|勃起]]狀態的[[陰莖|陰莖]]跟[[陰道|陰道]]互相接合及在內摩擦的過程<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.zdic.net/hans/%E6%80%A7%E4%BA%A4 |title=性交 汉典 |access-date=2020-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190618033654/https://www.zdic.net/hans/%25E6%2580%25A7%25E4%25BA%25A4 |archive-date=2019-06-18 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，主要目的是为了令自身獲得[[性快感|性快感]]、[[有性生殖|繁殖下一代]]<ref name="Most common">Sexual intercourse most commonly means penile–vaginal penetration for sexual pleasure and/or sexual reproduction; dictionary sources state that it especially means this, and scholarly sources over the years agree. See, for example;
