*{{cite book | author = Clint E. Bruess | author2 = Elizabeth Schroeder | title = Sexuality Education Theory and Practice | publisher = Jones & Bartlett Publishers | year = 2013 | page = 152 | accessdate = 2014-12-05 | isbn = 1449649289 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=WWFW6-kkAVoC&pg=PA152 | quote = Vaginal sex is defined as when a penis or sex toy is inserted into a vagina for pleasure. In many cultures around the world, vaginal sex is what is usually implied when people refer to 'having sex' or 'sexual intercourse.' It is the most frequently studied behavior and is often the focus of sexuality education programming for youth. | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150326113550/http://books.google.com/books?id=WWFW6-kkAVoC&pg=PA152 | archive-date = 2015-03-26 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。其他的[[插入式性行為|插入式性行為]]包括[[肛交|肛交]]（將陰莖與人類的肛門和直腸互相接合）、[[口交|口交]]（以口腔、舌、齒等部位刺激性伴侶的性器官）、[[指交|指交]]（以手指刺激性伴侶的性器官）、插入[[假陰莖|假陰莖]]（特別是[[捆綁式假陰莖|捆綁式假陰莖]]）至性器官<ref name="health.discovery.com">{{cite web | title=Sexual Intercourse | publisher=[[Discovery_Channel|Discovery.com]] | accessdate=2008-01-12 | url=http://health.discovery.com/centers/sex/sexpedia/intercourse.html | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080822040701/http://health.discovery.com/centers/sex/sexpedia/intercourse.html | archivedate=2008-08-22 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Kar">{{cite book|author=Nilamadhab Kar|author2=Gopal Chandra Kar|title=Comprehensive Textbook of Sexual Medicine|publisher=Jaypee Brothers Publishers|pages=107–112|isbn=8180614050|year=2005|accessdate=2012-09-04|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YxcjMPbGHQIC&pg=PA107|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131015130053/http://books.google.com/books?id=YxcjMPbGHQIC&pg=PA107|archive-date=2013-10-15|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Rutter and Pepper">{{Cite book|author=Virginia Rutter|author2=Pepper Schwartz|title=The Gender of Sexuality: Exploring Sexual Possibilities|year=2011|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield Publishers|page=76|isbn=0742570053|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Gorf-_nueAoC&pg=PA76|accessdate=2015-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150905080014/https://books.google.com/books?id=Gorf-_nueAoC&pg=PA76|archive-date=2015-09-05|dead-url=no}}</ref>。這些活動牽涉到個體與個體之間的[[身體親密|身體接觸]]，當事人通常能從中獲得身心之愉悅感，[[人類性行為|人類性行為]]亦有助加強人與人之間的[[感情纽带|感情纽带]]<ref name=health.discovery.com/><ref name="Freberg">{{Cite book|author=Laura Freberg|title=Discovering Biological Psychology|publisher=Cengage Learning|pages=308–310|isbn=0547177798|year=2009|accessdate=2016-01-09|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-zyTMXAjzQsC&pg=PA308|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160506153227/https://books.google.com/books?id=-zyTMXAjzQsC&pg=PA308|archive-date=2016-05-06|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

「性交或其他[[性活動|性活動]]包含什麽成分在內？」此一問題有着許多不同的看法及答案<ref name="Lerner">{{cite book | title = Handbook of Adolescent Psychology | publisher = John Wiley & Sons | year = 2004 | pages = 193–196 | accessdate = 2013-04-29 | isbn = 0471690449 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=_wXasY1HyAYC&pg=PA193 | quote = When researchers use the term ''sex'', they nearly always mean sexual intercourse – more specifically, penile–vaginal intercourse... The widespread, unquestioned equation of penile–vaginal intercourse with sex reflects a failure to examine systematically 'whether the respondent's understanding of the question matches what the researcher had in mind.' | author = Richard M. Lerner | author2 = Laurence Steinberg | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20131015065657/http://books.google.com/books?id=_wXasY1HyAYC&pg=PA193 | archive-date = 2013-10-15 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Carpenter">參見[https://books.google.com/books?id=6qNCeI2AcY4C&pg=PT11&lpg=PT11 第11頁] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6qNCeI2AcY4C&pg=PT11&lpg=PT11 |date=20161201151643 }}以及[https://books.google.com/books?id=pXXZn_qSoDoC&pg=PA48 第47-49頁] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pXXZn_qSoDoC&pg=PA48 |date=20161201074430 }}（有关如何界定「失貞」及性交和性活動的觀点、男同性戀者和女同性戀者如何定義失貞，以及有多少研究人員和異性戀者按有否進行陰莖－陰道交定義失貞的信息）{{Cite book|author=Laura M. Carpenter|title=Virginity Lost: An Intimate Portrait of First Sexual Experiences|publisher=NYU Press|year=2005|accessdate=2011-10-09|pages=295 pages|isbn=0-8147-1652-0|url=https://books.google.com/?id=pXXZn_qSoDoC}}</ref>，對此問題抱持的觀點亦可能影響当事人對[[性健康|性健康]]的看法<ref name="WHO, Sex">{{cite web|title=Defining sexual health: Report of a technical consultation on sexual health|publisher=[[World_Health_Organization|World Health Organization]]|date=2002-01|accessdate=2012-09-05|page=4|url=http://www.who.int/reproductivehealth/topics/gender_rights/defining_sexual_health.pdf|quote=In English, the term 'sex' is often used to mean 'sexual activity' and can cover a range of behaviours. Other languages and cultures use different terms, with slightly different meanings.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120906205203/http://www.who.int/reproductivehealth/topics/gender_rights/defining_sexual_health.pdf|archive-date=2012-09-06|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Who">{{cite web |title=Global strategy for the prevention and control of sexually transmitted infections: 2006–2015. Breaking the chain of transmission |publisher=[[World_Health_Organization|World Health Organization]] |year=2007 |accessdate=2011-11-26 |url=http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2007/9789241563475_eng.pdf |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722013750/http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2007/9789241563475_eng.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-22 }}</ref>。儘管性交一詞通常指的是陰莖－陰道交，和能產生[[后代|后代]]的交合<ref name="Most common"/>，但它亦普遍地代指带侵入成分的口交，以及陰莖－肛交，但代指后者的情況則較为常見<ref name="Oral and anal">*{{cite web | title=Sexual Intercourse | publisher=[[Discovery_Channel|Discovery.com]] | accessdate=2008-01-12 | url=http://health.discovery.com/centers/sex/sexpedia/intercourse.html | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080822040701/http://health.discovery.com/centers/sex/sexpedia/intercourse.html | archivedate=2008-08-22 | dead-url=no }}
*{{cite book|author=Nilamadhab Kar|author2=Gopal Chandra Kar|title=Comprehensive Textbook of Sexual Medicine|publisher=Jaypee Brothers Publishers|pages=107–112|isbn=8180614050|year=2005|accessdate=2012-09-04|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YxcjMPbGHQIC&pg=PA107|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131015130053/http://books.google.com/books?id=YxcjMPbGHQIC&pg=PA107|archive-date=2013-10-15|dead-url=no}}
*{{cite book| author = Nancy W. Denney| author2 = David Quadagno | title = Human Sexuality | publisher = Mosby-Year Book | year = 2008 | page = 273|isbn = 0801663741| url =|quote=Although the term intercourse is usually used to refer to the insertion of the penis into the vagina, it is also used to refer to oral intercourse or anal intercourse in which the penis is inserted into the mouth or the anus, respectively.}}</ref>。它通常由「插入與否」此一點來定義。而諸如不帶侵入成分的[[舔陰|舔陰]]、互相撫慰等非插入式性行為，則一般會被統稱為体外性行为（outercourse）<ref name="Non-penetrative">*{{Cite book| author = Ann O'Leary| title = Beyond Condoms: Alternative Approaches to HIV Prevention| isbn = 0306467313| publisher = Springer| year = 2002| page = 155| accessdate = 2013-08-21| url = https://books.google.com/books?id=J3NT39hW474C&pg=PA155| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20131231143701/http://books.google.com/books?id=J3NT39hW474C&pg=PA155| archive-date = 2013-12-31| dead-url = no}}
*{{Cite book| author = Paula Kamen| title = Her Way: Young Women Remake the Sexual Revolution| isbn = 0814747337| publisher = New York University Press| year = 2000| pages = 74–77| accessdate = 2012-09-05| url = https://books.google.com/?id=9bXq3Qc4py0C&pg=PA74&lpg=PA74}}
*{{cite book|title=The Person With HIV/AIDS: Nursing Perspectives|edition=3rd|isbn=8122300049|publisher=Springer Publishing Company|year=2000|page=103|accessdate=2012-01-29|url=https://books.google.com/?id=WSCQ4L8kSXsC&pg=PA103|author1=Jerry D. Durham|author2=Felissa R. Lashley}}</ref>。然而非插入式性行為在一些情況下亦會遭認作「性交」<ref name=health.discovery.com/><ref name="Kahn, Fawcett">{{cite book|title = The Encyclopedia of Mental Health | publisher = Infobase Publishing | year = 2008 | page = 111| accessdate =2012-09-05 |isbn = 0816064547| url = https://books.google.com/?id=tTFYIh-HcYYC&pg=PA111&lpg=PA111|author1=Ada P. Kahn |author2=Jan Fawcett }}</ref>。「性愛」（sex）一詞通常是在代指性交，但其亦可指任何形式的性活动<ref name="WHO, Sex"/><ref name="Randall">{{cite journal|title=What is sex? Students' definitions of having sex, sexual partner, and unfaithful sexual behaviour|journal=The Canadian Journal of Human Sexuality|volume=12|issue=|pages=87–96|year=2003|pmid=|doi=|url=http://www.questia.com/googleScholar.qst?docId=5002088390|quote=Recently, researchers in the United States, the United Kingdom, and Australia have investigated university students' definitions of having sex. These studies found that students differ in their opinions of what sexual behaviours constitute having sex (Pitts & Rahman, 2001; Richters & Song, 1999; Sanders & Reinisch, 1999). While the vast majority of respondents (more than 97%) in these three studies included penile–vaginal intercourse in their definition of sex, fewer (between 70% and 90%) respondents considered penile–anal intercourse to constitute having sex. Oral-genital behaviours were defined as sex by between 32% and 58% of respondents.|author=Randall, H. E.|author2=Byers, S. E.|last-author-amp=yes}}</ref>。	
因為人們可從像性交般的性行為感染[[性傳播疾病|性傳播疾病]]的缘故<ref name="Hales">{{Cite book|author=Dianne Hales|title=An Invitation to Health Brief 2010–2011|publisher=Cengage Learning|year=2008|accessdate=2013-08-29|pages=269–271|isbn=0495391921|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oP91HVIMPRIC&pg=PA269|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131231143640/http://books.google.com/books?id=oP91HVIMPRIC&pg=PA269|archive-date=2013-12-31|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Kumar">{{Cite book|author=Bhushan Kumar|author2=Somesh Gupta|title=Sexually Transmitted Infections|publisher=Elsevier Health Sciences|year=2014|accessdate=2014-12-06|page=237|isbn=8131229785|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kQ9tAwAAQBAJ&pg=PT237|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150326130715/http://books.google.com/books?id=kQ9tAwAAQBAJ&pg=PT237|archive-date=2015-03-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>，所以[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]建议人們應實行[[安全性行為|安全性行為]]<ref name="Who"/>，儘管非插入式性行為能顯著降低從中感染的風險<ref name="Who"/><ref name="CDC">{{cite web| title = Sexually Transmitted Disease Surveillance| publisher = [[Centers_for_Disease_Control_and_Prevention|Centers for Disease Control and Prevention]] (CDC)| year = 2008| accessdate = 2011-12-06| url = http://www.cdc.gov/std/stats08/surv2008-Complete.pdf| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20111203004357/http://www.cdc.gov/std/stats08/surv2008-Complete.pdf| archive-date = 2011-12-03| dead-url = no}} 另請參見[http://www.cdc.gov/std/stats08/2008survFactSheet.PDF 实况报道] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cdc.gov/std/stats08/2008survFactSheet.PDF |date=20170222010911 }}</ref>。

在人类社会中，许多国家对性行为都有着某种的法律限制，比如[[近親性交|近親性交]]、與[[未成年人|未成年人]]、[[動物戀|動物]]、[[性交易|性工作者]]、[[强奸|非自願者]]發生的性行為，以至[[同性性行為|同性性行為]]、[[婚前性行為|婚前性行為]]、[[婚外性行為|婚外性行為]]。[[宗教|宗教]]信仰在與性行為有關的抉擇中亦扮演了一定的角色，比如與[[处女|处女]]相关的抉擇<ref name="Carpenter"/><ref name="Intimate">{{Cite book|author1=Bryan Strong |author2=Christine DeVault |author3=Theodore F. Cohen |title=The Marriage and Family Experience: Intimate Relationship in a Changing Society| publisher = Cengage Learning|year = 2010|accessdate=2011-10-08 |page = 186| isbn = 0-534-62425-1|url=https://books.google.com/?id=qjvoSOMB5JMC&pg=PA186|quote=Most people agree that we maintain virginity as long as we refrain from sexual (vaginal) intercourse. But occasionally we hear people speak of 'technical virginity' [...] Data indicate that 'a very significant proportion of teens ha[ve] had experience with oral sex, even if they haven't had sexual intercourse, and may think of themselves as virgins' [...] Other research, especially research looking into virginity loss, reports that 35% of virgins, defined as people who have never engaged in vaginal intercourse, have nonetheless engaged in one or more other forms of heterosexual sexual activity (e.g., oral sex, anal sex, or mutual masturbation).}}</ref>，以及相關的法律和公共政策。不同[[宗教與性|宗教及教派对性的看法]]差異很大，雖然當中亦有相同之處，比如對[[通奸|通奸]]的反對及禁止。

